<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="simply-adv">simply <strong><em>adv</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'sɪmpli/    美 /'sɪmpli/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>简单地；简明地：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>To put it simply</strong>, computer skills are vital to today’s learners and tomorrow’s bread-winners. 
简而言之，计算机技能对今天的学习者以及将来要养家糊口的人而言都是至关重要的。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The book explains grammar simply and clearly.
这本书对语法解释得简洁明了。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>朴素地；简朴地</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>live simply
简朴地生活</p></div>

<h4 id="3-just">3.★ <strong>仅仅；只不过：(just)</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Staying with a native speaker is better for children than simply sitting in a classroom.
对于孩子来说，与讲母语的人呆在一起比仅仅坐在教室里要好。</p><footer>2014 全国</footer></div>

<h4 id="4">4.<strong>完全；简直；根本：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I simply don’t know.
我完全不知道。</p><footer>人教③ – 3</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Running a company is not <strong><em>_</em></strong> (simple) a matter of hiring people — they also need to be trained.  （2008 浙江改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. simply  </p></div>